    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-10-06T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-10-06T05:00:00-05:00" n="981"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d981">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1163 Am 3/630: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-10-06T19:00:00+09:00"
                            >October 6, 1941—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 9—3:27 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1576. Department’s 627, September 29, 11 a.m. [<hi rend="italic">p.m.</hi>]
                    Japanese violent attack against American Catholic Missionaries in Kwangtung.
                    After preparing a strongly worded first person note dated October 3, enclosing
                    with it a copy of most of Bishop Paschang’s letter dated August 5 to the
                    American Consul General at Canton, I sent directly to the Foreign Office with a
                    personal letter referring to his expressed wish to have such cases brought to
                    his personal attention, and asking his intercession in preventing future similar
                    incidents. See my telegram no. 1249 dated August [15, 10 p.m.]<note n="67"
                        xml:id="d981fn1">Not printed, but see Ambassador Grew’s memorandum of August
                        15, <ref target="frus1931-41v01#pg_911">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 911</ref>.</note> and despatch no. 5791,
                    of August 18.<note n="68" xml:id="d981fn2">Not printed; for its enclosures,
                        dated August 15 and 16, see <ref target="frus1931-41v01#pg_911">
                            <hi rend="italic">ibid.</hi>, pp. 911</ref> and <ref
                            target="frus1931-41v01#pg_913">913</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Sent to the Department via Peiping. Peiping please repeat to Chungking and
                    Canton.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
